Executive Value Breakdown — Lunar Thermal Blanket
Phase 3 (Theory-Only)

Audience: Executives, Program Managers, Finance, Risk

Scope Rule: This document explains where value comes from in time, money, and risk terms. It does not claim performance numbers or guarantee savings. All values are directional and comparative.

Total Internal Development Cost (Before Any Hardware Exists)

Estimated Total:
$600,000 – $1.4 million

This estimate does not include:

prototype fabrication

environmental testing

lunar deployment

integration delays

redesign cycles caused by thermal edge cases

This cost represents engineering time, analysis, modeling, and program churn required to independently rediscover a passive lunar thermal buffering solution.

